<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--UnscheduledLanding     02-29 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Unscheduled Landing,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Smoke In Jet Cockpit Forces Unscheduled Landing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GAINESVILLE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Smoke in the cockpit of a Chicago-bound
Midway Airlines jet forced its pilot to make an unscheduled landing
here, officials said.
   No injuries were reported among the 119 passengers and five crew
members aboard Flight 793, which originated in Tampa, authorities
said.
   Sunday's landing of the Boeing-737 was a precautionary measure,
said V.H. Steed of the Federal Aviation Administration in Atlanta.
   The smoke was created by an electrical problem, said Sandra
Allen, director of corporate communications for the Chicago-based
Midway Airlines.
   Passenger Jon Klank, 24, of Glen Ellyn, Ill., said he was
sleeping when the plane started to descend to Gainesville Regional
Airport.
   ``I woke up when the ladies next to me started crying,'' he said.
   Midway treated the passengers to lunch while they awaited
another jet to take them to Chicago.
</TEXT>
