<HEAD>Police Say Reports Of Tainted Milk A Hoax</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WICHITA, Kan. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Reports that condoms were discovered in
some milk products of Steffen Dairy Foods Co. were a hoax to
defraud the company and not a case of tampering at the plant,
police say.
   Four people have been arrested on charges of felony theft and
conspiracy to commit felony theft, police Capt. John Dotson said
Saturday. More suspects were being sought, he said.
   ``Reports by four people of condoms in their milk was a hoax,''
Dotson said. ``There is no tampering of products at Steffen.''
   Steffen recalled about 10,000 quart and half-gallon cardboard
milk cartons Wednesday after four reports about unpackaged condoms
in the milk. The company received a fifth report last week, but
that was retracted, Dotson said.
