candidates scored in the ``good'' or ``excellent'' categories.
   ``These candidates debate about many important issues, but they
neglect to address the environment,'' said Patty Frase, a member of
the Arkansas Enviromental Congress who attended the weekend
conference. ``How can we focus on national defense when we can't
defend out drinking water supplies against chemicals that cause
birth defects and cancer?''
