<HEAD>Says Evangelists Are Gettting A Bad Name</HEAD>
<NOTE>EDS: Adds four grafs background</NOTE>
<HEAD>With PM-Swaggart</HEAD>
<DATELINE>COLUMBUS, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Oral Roberts told a church service that
some people are trying to embarrass evangelists and ruin their
ministries.
   ``Right now, this old world and the media and certain church
people are dragging the name of evangelists in the mud,'' said the
70-year Roberts.
   Roberts, of Tulsa, Okla., mentioned no one by name when he spoke
to more than 1,200 people Sunday at the Christian Center in
suburban Gahanna.
   Television evangelist Jimmy Swaggart was disciplined by the
Assemblies of God last week after confessing to unspecified sinful
behavior against his wife. Jim Bakker left his national television
ministry last year after he admitted having an extramarital sexual
encounter with church secretary Jessica Hahn.
   Roberts made a controversial appeal last year for $8 million,
saying that God would ``call me home'' if he did not raise the
money to fund scholarships for medical missionaries.
   Oral Roberts University said last month that 117 scholarships
had been funded, but that there were no plans to raise funds for
additional aid.
   In December, Roberts pulled his weekly ``Expect a Miracle''
program from 71 stations, but continued to run it on 150 others.
   ``Our income dropped off in May and it stayed there,'' his
spokeswoman, Jan Dargatz, said at the time. ``That's when the Jim
and Tammy thing heated up. There is a correlation there.''
</TEXT>
