   Republicans claim Lautenberg, seeking his second six-year term,
is among the most vulnerable incumbents in the Senate. Democrats
counter that the millionaire businessman has compiled an impressive
record.
   Dawkins has never sought elected office, but has spent more than
a year planting the seeds of his candidacy around the state.
