<HEAD>Five Die In Suspicious Fire</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 5 grafs, possible murder-suicide, picking up 5th
graf pvs, ``It's the entire xxx</NOTE>
<DATELINE>GROVELAND, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   All five members of one family were found
dead early today in their burning home, and authorities said
investigators were treating the deaths as homicides.
   ``They were obviously not killed by the fire,'' said Livingston
County Sheriff Richard Kane. He said that it might have been a
murder-suicide, and that a 16-gauge shotgun was found near the
father's body.
   ``Obviously, two scenarios come to mind: murder-suicide is one,
and the other is that another person was involved in committing
these acts,'' said Kane.
   The fire, discovered just before midnight by neighbors, was
``highly suspicious,'' Kane said.
   Kane identified the victims as Lawrence Delabarto, 32; his wife,
Linda, also 32; and their children, Anthony, 12, Danielle 10, and
Dominic, 6. He said the three young children and the father were
found shot; Mrs. Delaberto was apparently strangled.
   ``It's the entire family,'' Kane said. ``They were all dead.''
   Firefighters in this hamlet about 10 miles south of Geneseo
found the five bodies in their bedrooms, Kane said.
   Kevin Niedermaier, chief of the Groveland Volunteer Fire
Department, said it took two hours to bring the fire under control.
   The father of the family worked for a wholesale liquor company
in the area, Kane said.
</TEXT>
