<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--Kenya-Accident     02-29 0148</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Kenya-Accident,0153</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>25 Killed, 26 Injured In Highway Crash</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAKURU, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three vehicles packed with people crashed
on a rain-slickened highway Monday, killing 25 people and injuring
26 others, authorities said.
   Many of the victims were supporters of political candidates
going to Nakuru to see the office-seekers present papers for the
March 21 general election.
   According to witnesses, one overcrowded pickup truck tried to
pass another, but rammed into an oncoming minibus.
   The injured were taken to Nakuru Provincial General Hospital,
where 11 were admitted and 15 were treated and released.
   The accident occurred about 8 a.m. on a road outside Nakuru,
which is 100 miles northwest of Nairobi.
   Small covered pickup trucks and minibuses or vans are the most
popular form of public transportation in Kenya. The brightly
colored vehicles, known as ``matatus,'' are criticized as
deathtraps because of their overcrowding and reckless drivers.
</TEXT>
