<1ST_LINE>r a AM-HighwayMurder     02-29 0274</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Highway Murder,0280</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Law Student Shot To Death Driving to Post-Bar Exam Party</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HALLANDALE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Police Monday looked for suspects who
apparently fired a shot from a van on Interstate 95, killing a man
on his way to a party after taking the Florida Bar exam.
   Irv Ribler, 26, was shot just below his left shoulder Saturday.
His car sped across the median, three lanes of oncoming traffic and
plowed into a gully.
   Friends following Ribler's car told police the shot was fired
from a van whose occupants had just thrown a small object at the
victim's sportscar, but that was unconfirmed, Broward County
Sheriff's spokesman Jim Leljedal said Sunday.
   No other traffic hit Ribler's car and no other injuries were
reported.
   ``He left me a note before he left Saturday,'' Ribler's mother,
Zaida Ribler, said Sunday. ``It says, `Mom, see you in the morning.
I love you. Irv.'
   ``He was a good son. He studied so hard. He worked in the yard.
He cleaned the house. He didn't drink,'' said his mother, who
cleaned houses and worked as a tailor seven days a week to put her
only child through Florida State University and the University of
Miami Law School. ``Now my life has ended. Everything is over.''
   Ribler was graduated from law school in May and initially failed
the bar exam. Since then, he had studied constantly. After taking
the test Wednesday, he was elated, certain he had passed, friends
said.
   ``His whole life was centered on passing the bar and working as
a public defender,'' said classmate Manny Fernandez, 24. ``He had
some offers. He was almost there.''
</TEXT>
