<1ST_LINE>r a AM-Cab-Sidewalk     02-29 0187</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Cab-Sidewalk,0192</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Cab Jumps Curb, Four Pedestrians and Driver Injured</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto HT2</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HOUSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A cab jumped a downtown sidewalk Monday and
struck four pedestrians before it slammed into a pole, authorities
said. All four pedestrians and the driver were hospitalized.
   The pedstrians were standing on the sidewalk waiting for a light
to change, police investigator J.M. Smith said.
   ``When we first arrived here, one of the victims was under the
cab,'' police officer J.A. Miller said. ``Myself and a couple of
citizens lifted the cab off her, and pulled her out.''
   The 29-year-old driver, whose name was not released, was unable
to explain what happened, and was taken to Ben Taub Hospital for
treatment, Smith said. Charges might be filed following further
investigation.
   Juanita Barrett, 42, was listed in good condition, while
Gertrudis Abdel-Khaliq, 37, was listed in guarded condition at
Hermann Hospital, a spokeswoman said. Anna Hornac 66, was listed in
stable condition at St. Luke's Hospital, a spokeswoman said.
   Dianna Bradford, 41, underwent surgery Monday night at Ben Taub
Hospital, and a hospital spokeswoman would say only that she was
``doing fine.''
