<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BusSuspect     02-29 0221</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Bus Suspect,0228</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Passenger Subdues Bus Robbery Suspect</HEAD>
<HEAD>LaserPhoto PX6</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAMDEN, N.J. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man armed with a toy gun tried to rob a
bus but was overpowered by a passenger who pushed him out the door
and held him on the ground until police arrived, officials said
Monday.
   The suspect, Leon Reddick, 32, of Camden, was charged with
robbery following the attempted holdup Sunday, said Camden Police
Lt. Thomas Long. He was in critical but stable condition at Cooper
University Medical Center with a head injury, a hospital
spokeswoman said.
   Long said a man boarded a New Jersey Transit bus, showed a gun
and demanded money from the bus driver, Jeannette Rodriguez.
   ``She hit the brakes, he fell forward,'' Long said.
   The hapless robber first hit his head on the windshield when he
fell. Then passenger William Bonet approached, Long said.
   ``He grabbed Reddick and struck him in the head several times
with the gun, which turned out to be plastic and broke,'' Long
said. The man fell out of the bus when the door opened and struck
his head on the ground, Long said.
   Bonet, whose age and address were not disclosed, then held the
man on the ground until police arrived, Long said.
   No charges were filed against Bonet.
   ``We told him, `Atta boy,''' Long said.
</TEXT>
