<TEXT>
   Police arrested a Jewish settler in connection
with the shooting deaths of two Arabs in the West Bank, and Israeli
Cabinet ministers suggested closing the occupied lands to media
coverage.
   The settler, from Neve Tzuf, was arrested Sunday, according to
Adi Gonen, national police spokesman. The man, whose name was not
