<1ST_LINE>s i BC-APN--AmazonDenizens Adv13   02-29 0344</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-APN--Amazon Denizens, Adv 13,0361</2ND_LINE>
<NOTE>$adv13</NOTE>
<HEAD>AGENCIES AND RADIO OUT</HEAD>
<NOTE>For Release Sunday, March 13</NOTE>
<HEAD>From AP Newsfeatures</HEAD>
<HEAD>With BC-APN--Amazing Amazon</HEAD>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By HUGH A. MULLIGAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Special Correspondent</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   BELEM, Brazil _ Some droll, delightful or deadly denizens of the
Amazon rain forest:
   Anaconda _ The world's super snake, a 38-foot constrictor that
suffocates rather than crushes its prey, the distinction usually
being lost on the victim.
   Bushmaster _ Twelve feet of vicious, venomous viper.
   Capybara _ King rat, 4 feet from pointy nose to lack of a tail.
   Crested toucan _ Birdland's Pinocchio, the perennial cover star
of nature magazines and travel folders.
   Dinoponera gigantea _ World's biggest ant at 1{ inches long.
   Electric eel _ It's a carp, not an eel, delivering 640 volts,
enough to power a commuter train. Indians believe its most jarring
jolt is saved for fishermen who catch more than they need.
   Fer-de-lance _ Hissing cousin of the copperhead, but faster and
fiercer with the fang.
   Jaguar _ This loud-mouthed cat out-roars and out-runs the larger
lion and tiger.
   Manatee _ Harmless, hapless and hunted, a flippered,
whale-tailed mammal that grazes on waterlilies; known locally as
the sea cow.
   Morpho didius _ Monarch of all the butterflies with a 7-inch
wingspread.
   Peccary _ A red-eared distant relation of the wild hog, cute but
pugnacious.
   Paiche _ A 400-pound catfish, succulent but seldom pan-ready.
   Piranha _ Only 4 to 15 inches, these ravenous, razor-toothed
fish, with a school enrollment into the thousands, can skeletonize
a cow or a cowhand in a matter of minutes.
   Tapir _ A lumbering, leathery mixture of hog and rhino that's
got to be seen, but not up too closely, to be believed.
   Three-toed sloth _ Upside down tree-snoozing quadruped of
legendary lethargy; may be self-endangered for preferring siesta to
sex.
   Titanus giganteus _ A half-foot long, hard-shelled beetle, the
global giant of its genus.
   Vampire bat _ Count Dracula's late-night drinking buddy with a
thirst for blood light; its dagger-sharp central incisors spread
rabies throughout the Amazon.
</TEXT>
<NOTE>End Adv for Sunday, March 13</NOTE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
