<1ST_LINE>r f AM-PenneyMove     02-29 0137</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Penney Move,0143</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Penney Putting Headquarters Building Up for Sale</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   J.C. Penney Co. Inc., which is vacating its
mid-Manhattan office tower and moving its headquarters operations
to Dallas, said Monday it was putting the 45-story building up for
sale.
   There was no asking price for the building, located at Sixth
Avenue and 53rd Street near the Rockefeller Center complex, said
Harvey McCormick, a Penney spokesman.
   The entire structure will be left vacant by the move, which
began in December and is expected to be completed by the end of
June, McCormick said.
   More than 1,200 of Penney's 2,200 management employees were
expected to ultimately move with the company to Texas, the
spokesman said. A ``very small percentage'' of 1,600 non-management
workers, who include secretaries and clerical workers, also were
transferring, he said.
</TEXT>
