<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Anheuser-SoftDrinks     02-29 0196</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Anheuser-Soft Drinks,0203</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Anheuser-Busch To Sell Sparkling Water, Soft Drink Brands</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. LOUIS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Anheuser-Busch Beverage Group Inc. announced
Monday that its aSante and Saratoga sparkling water brands and its
Zeltzer Seltzer natural soda brand are up for sale.
   The decision follows the company's recent discontinuance of the
Dewey Stevens wine cooler brand due to a declining rate of growth
industrywide in cooler sales.
   Terry Poulos, vice president and general manager of the group,
said that without the Dewey Stevens sales, ``total Beverage Group
volume was reduced below the level necessary to financially support
our continued production of these brands.''
   Anheuser-Busch will continue to support the brands through
current distributors until they are sold, Poulos said.
   He also said that since the introduction of the non-beer
beverages, competitive distribution methods had changed from the
primary use of wholesalers to direct shipments from producers to
major retailers. Therefore, the brands no longer fit
Anheuser-Busch's wholesaler system as originally envisioned, he
said.
   The company will continue to market Master Cellars keg wines and
Anheuser & Fehrs, an imported German wine. The test marketing of
the imported Ballygowan Irish sparkling spring water also will
continue, Poulos said.
</TEXT>
