<HEAD>Simon & Schuster Buys Travel Books from Rand McNally</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Simon & Schuster Inc. said Monday it had
acquired a group of travel publications from Rand McNally & Co. for
an undisclosed price.
   The Gulf & Western Co. publishing and information services unit
said it had acquired Rand McNally's campground directories and
national park guides and other travel location products including
the Places Rated series, which rates cities according to
quality-of-life attributes.
   Rand McNally retains its map-related travel publications.
   The titles will become part of Simon & Schuster's Prentice Hall
Trade division which publishes and distributes travel guides and
other travel-related products under such imprints as Access,
Frommer and Mobil.
   Steven Murphy, president of Prentice Hall, said the acquisitions
represent ``a perfect fit in terms of product and strategy.''
   ``It will not only add new destinations to our travel title list
but will greatly enhance our capabilities in the development of new
product for the travel market,'' he said.
   Roger Wildermuth, president of the Rand McNally publishing
group, said the divestiture is part of a strategy of concentrating
its consumer publishing resources on road atlases, road maps, world
atlases and other map products.
